The article discusses the continuation of a national emergency declaration made by President Biden in 2017 regarding serious human rights abuse and corruption around the world. The President states that the prevalence and severity of these issues pose a significant threat to the national security, foreign policy, and economy of the United States. As a result, the national emergency declared in 2017 will continue for another year. This notice will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress. The article is dated December 12, 2022.